    "faq": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question-1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What Makes Titan Battlegear <em>The Safest?</em>",
            "text": "<p>Titan Battlegear's hockey neck guard utilizes advanced American-made cut-resistant materials and a unique collar design to maximize coverage of critical zones.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "full_text",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Other Brands Use Kevlar®, Why Titan Cut Resistance is Better?",
            "text": "<p>Most <strong>Kevlar® fabrics offer an ISO 13997:1999 blade cut resistance level 2</strong>, and in very rare occasions level 3 (on a scale of 1 to 5).</p><p><strong>Titan's hockey neck guard shirt utilizes proprietary, American made fabrics, delivering the highest cut-resistance: level A9</strong>, which makes it 200 stronger than steel, and almost 5 times more cut resistant than Kevlar® products rated level 3 at 5N.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Are there certifications for the USA Hockey mandated laceration protection?",
            "text": "<p>Unfortunately <strong>USA hockey does not have any certification requirements</strong> currently.</p><p>They state “Players are required to wear a neck laceration protector that is commercially designed and manufactured for that purpose.”</p><p>We are eager for them to enforce stricter guidelines around the level of protection to qualify as “neck laceration protectors” for the Aug 1, 2024 mandate.</p><p>In our <strong>testing of other products available in the market, we revealed a very low level of cut resistance</strong> due to materials such as Kevlar®, which only provide a level 2 or 3 cut-resistance, depending on fabric weight.</p><p>Titan shirts achieve up to a level A9 cut-resistance, <strong>the highest level of cut protection in the world.</strong></p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How Safe Is The Shirt After Many Washes?",
            "text": "<p>We tested cleaning with cycles across TEN Durawash twin-tub industrial machines. This is equivalent to 50 washes in a domestic washing machine.</p><p><strong>The cut resistance level, following this washing process increased by 4%.</strong> Test reports from INTERTEK are available upon request.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Where Are Titan's Products Produced?",
            "text": "<p><strong>Titan was born in South Florida, and Built in the Americas</strong>. Our factories are in Winter Park, Florida, and Colombia. We source material from premium partners in the USA.</p><p><strong>The mass market and other independent brands produce in China</strong>, with questionable labor practices and superficial cut resistance certifications.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_x6e9JG": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I Customize Titan's Hockey Neck Guard Shirt With My Team Logo/Colors?",
            "text": "<p><strong>Yes</strong>, Titan's <a href=\"/pages/teamworks2\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Teamworks\">TeamWorks</a> program offers custom gear for teams, as well as personalization by player, including name, number, and even their country flag to represent their nationality!</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "contact": {
          "type": "contact",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Didn’t find your answer?",
            "text": "<p>Don't hestitate to contact us</p>",
            "show_phone": false,
            "avatar_height": 60,
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
